  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of quantitative engagement metrics, \"A Constellation of Courts,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2021, demonstrates a notable commitment to research integrity and policy relevance, suggesting an underlying potential for impact in legal studies.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published in 2021 by Leuven University Press, \"A Constellation of Courts\" has not received any formal citations or community discourse in traditional platforms. However, the absence of these metrics does not diminish the book's significance, as it has been clearly positioned within the framework of commercial linkage. The presence of links on platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads indicates an engagement with a reading audience outside of academia, suggesting that the work may resonate with practitioners and enthusiasts of legal studies.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book also demonstrates a connection to sustainability and policy relevance, as evidenced by its classification under a UN Sustainable Development Goal. This aspect reveals that the material discussed in the book is not merely theoretical but may have implications for real-world legal issues, thereby enhancing its relevance to both scholars and policymakers.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Additionally, the identification of commercial linkage suggests that there may be a broader public interest in the themes explored in the book. This underscores the potential for the work to contribute to ongoing dialogues within the legal community and beyond, especially in areas where law intersects with societal needs and issues.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Although there are no direct metrics for high-fidelity social and community discourse available, the latent signals of commercial interest and policy connectivity highlight the importance of this scholarly output in creating dialogue around contemporary legal matters. As the legal field increasingly embraces interdisciplinary approaches, works like \"A Constellation of Courts\" will be instrumental in guiding future discussions and research directions.</p>",
